s of pittsburgh randy holds a bachelor’s degree in chemistry from hiram college and a master’s degree in polymer science and engineering from case western reserve university in cleveland stevan r schott executive vice president of advanced materials manufacturing and equipment division stevan schott steve joined calgon carbon in  as executive director of finance in  he was promoted to vice president of finance and was responsible for the companys us and asia accounting tax treasury planning and risk management functions as well as all external financial reporting in  he was promoted to vice president chief financial officer with responsibility for all corporate financial functions prior to joining calgon carbon steve spent eight years at duquesne light holdings inc a conglomerate whose primary business was electric energy during his eightyear tenure he held various positions including controller vice president of finance and chief financial officer steve also spent  years at deloitte  touche where he was a senior manager in the auditing practice steve holds a bs in business administration from duquesne university james a coccagno executive vice president of core carbon and services division james a coccagno jim joined calgon carbon in september  as vice president  global procurement and strategic initiatives he is responsible for the sourcing of all goods and services for calgon carbon around the globe he is also responsible for corporate strategic projects including ma prior to joining the company jim held several positions of increasing responsibility in procurement logistics compliance corporate communications and corporate development at lanxess corporation a specialty chemicals company from  to  during his last assignment at lanxess corporation jim led the integration of three acquisitions in an eighteen month period jim began his career at bayer corporation in  and remained there until  working in supply chain management sales marketing and procurement jim hol